  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Associate (Outsource)",
  "description": "<p>Job Title: Accounts Associate (Outsource)</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Handle full sets of accounts for a portfolio of clients in various industries.</li><li>Prepare monthly or quarterly financial reports for management and reporting purposes.</li><li>Ensure firms’ service standards and reporting deadlines are met.</li><li>Prepare GST report and filing.</li><li>Prepare unaudited statutory financial statements in accordance with SFRS.</li><li>Payroll processing, such as calculating payroll and submitting CPF for clients.</li><li>Other related accounting tasks as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Position Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Work independently with minimal supervision.</li><li>Preferably a Diploma or Degree in Accounting and Finance or pursuing relevant professional qualifications.</li><li>Handling a portfolio of clients, those with project-related experiences will be advantageous.</li><li>Possess a strong understanding of the SFRS, GST Act and related regulatory policies.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office applications and accounting software such as Quickbook, Xero, etc.</li><li>Good command of English and Chinese both written and spoken.</li><li>Meticulous with a strong sense of responsibility, proactive, and able to take initiative to perform duties independently and able to work collaboratively as a team.</li><li>Good interpersonal skills and ability to communicate effectively with clients.</li></ul>",
